# AI-Guided Self-Reflection Session Platform
## System Design & Technical Specification — MVP

**Prepared for:** Client  
**Prepared by:** AsapStudio  
**Date:** March 2026  
**Version:** 1.0 (MVP)

---

## 1. Project Overview

### What We're Building
A web-based platform where an **AI avatar** guides users through structured self-reflection sessions. The avatar acts as a compassionate listener — asking pre-defined questions, listening to responses, and gently guiding the conversation forward.

### Key Principles
- **AI does NOT give advice** — it follows scripts and listens
- **AI does NOT search the internet** — fully scripted flow
- **Human-driven** — the user reflects, discovers, and gains personal insight
- **Safe space** — no judgment, no labeling, no diagnosis
- **Not therapy** — but uses therapeutic process design

### MVP Scope (This Phase)
- ✅ One pre-defined question script (5–6 questions)
- ✅ AI avatar asks questions and listens to responses
- ✅ Re-ask logic if user's response is unclear or off-topic
- ✅ Full session transcript stored in database
- ✅ Doctor can view completed session transcripts
- ✅ Target latency: **< 1.5 seconds** response time

---

## 2. System Architecture

### High-Level Flow

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "User's Browser"
        A["User with Mic 🎤"] --> B[WebRTC Connection]
        B --> C["Avatar Video Display 👤"]
    end

    subgraph "Real-Time Pipeline Server"
        B <-->|WebRTC| D[Pipecat Pipeline]
        D --> E[Deepgram STT]
        E --> F[LLM Brain]
        F --> G[Cartesia TTS]
        G --> H[Simli Avatar]
        H --> D
    end

    subgraph "Backend Server"
        F <--> I[FastAPI]
        I --> J[(MongoDB)]
    end

    subgraph "Doctor Access"
        J --> K["Doctor Dashboard 🩺"]
    end
```

### How a Session Works (Step by Step)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User (Browser)
    participant Avatar as Simli Avatar
    participant STT as Deepgram (Ears)
    participant LLM as GPT-4o-mini (Brain)
    participant TTS as Cartesia (Voice)
    participant DB as MongoDB

    Note over User,DB: Session Starts
    LLM->>TTS: "Hello! How are you feeling right now?"
    TTS->>Avatar: Speech audio
    Avatar->>User: Avatar speaks with lip-sync

    User->>STT: Speaks response
    STT->>LLM: "I've been stressed about work"
    LLM->>DB: Save Q&A exchange
    
    Note over LLM: Decides: ACKNOWLEDGE + NEXT QUESTION
    LLM->>TTS: "Thank you for sharing. What has been weighing on you?"
    TTS->>Avatar: Speech audio
    Avatar->>User: Avatar responds naturally

    Note over User,DB: Loop continues through all questions
    
    Note over LLM: All questions complete
    LLM->>TTS: "Thank you for this session. Take care."
    LLM->>DB: Finalize session
```

