## 3. Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Why This Choice |
|-----------|-----------|-----------------|
| **Real-time Pipeline** | **Pipecat** (Python) | Open-source framework for real-time voice AI bots. Handles audio/video streaming, turn-taking, and all service integrations out of the box |
| **Avatar** | **Simli** | Converts speech audio → lip-synced avatar video in real-time |
| **Speech-to-Text** | **Deepgram** (Nova-3) | Industry-leading streaming STT with ~200ms latency |
| **Text-to-Speech** | **Cartesia** (Sonic) | Ultra-low latency TTS (~200ms), natural-sounding voices |
| **LLM (Brain)** | **GPT-4o-mini** via LangChain | Fast, cost-effective, follows scripted instructions accurately |
| **Backend API** | **FastAPI** (Python) | REST API for session management, doctor dashboard |
| **Database** | **MongoDB** | Flexible document storage for sessions, messages, and Q&A |
| **Transport** | **WebRTC** | Real-time audio/video streaming between browser and server |
| **Voice Detection** | **Silero VAD** (built-in to Pipecat) | Detects when user starts/stops speaking for natural turn-taking |

### What is Pipecat?

Pipecat is an **open-source Python framework** for building real-time voice and video AI agents. Instead of manually wiring together STT → LLM → TTS → Avatar (which takes weeks), Pipecat provides a **pipeline** where data flows through each stage automatically and in parallel:

```python
pipeline = Pipeline([
    transport.input(),         # Captures user's mic audio
    stt,                       # Deepgram: audio → text (streaming)
    llm,                       # GPT-4o-mini: decides response (streaming)
    tts,                       # Cartesia: text → speech audio (streaming)
    simli_avatar,              # Simli: audio → lip-synced video
    transport.output(),        # Sends video + audio back to browser
])
```

**Key benefit:** Everything streams in parallel — while the LLM is generating words, the TTS is already converting earlier words to speech, and Simli is already rendering video. This is how we achieve **< 1.5 second response time**.

