## 5. Session Logic

### LLM Decision Engine

For each user response, the LLM decides **one action**:

| Action | When | Avatar Response Example |
|--------|------|------------------------|
| **NEXT** | Clear, relevant response | "Thank you. Now, what has been on your mind today?" |
| **REASK** | Unclear, too brief, off-topic | "That's okay. Take your time — how would you describe what you're feeling?" |
| **ACKNOWLEDGE** | Emotional or vulnerable response | "Thank you for sharing that. It takes courage." → then next question |
| **CLOSE** | All questions completed | "Thank you for this session. I hope it was a moment of reflection." |

### LLM Rules (Strictly Enforced)

| ✅ ALWAYS | ❌ NEVER |
|-----------|---------|
| Follow the script sequence | Give advice or opinions |
| Keep responses short (1–2 sentences) | Search the internet |
| Acknowledge the user warmly | Diagnose or label feelings |
| Be gentle when re-asking | Provide solutions or suggestions |
| Stay on topic | Reference external information |

### Pre-defined Script Example

```json
{
  "script_name": "Daily Check-In",
  "questions": [
    {"order": 1, "text": "How are you feeling right now, in this moment?", "category": "opening"},
    {"order": 2, "text": "What has been occupying your thoughts today?", "category": "exploration"},
    {"order": 3, "text": "When you think about that, what emotion comes up for you?", "category": "deep_reflection"},
    {"order": 4, "text": "Have you experienced this feeling before? When was that?", "category": "deep_reflection"},
    {"order": 5, "text": "What would you say to a friend going through the same thing?", "category": "perspective"},
    {"order": 6, "text": "As we wrap up, what is one thing you would like to carry forward?", "category": "closing"}
  ]
}
```

