## 6. Database Design (MongoDB)

### `sessions` — One document per session
```json
{
  "_id": "session_abc123",
  "patient_name": "John Doe",
  "script_name": "Daily Check-In",
  "status": "completed",
  "started_at": "2026-03-07T10:00:00Z",
  "ended_at": "2026-03-07T10:12:30Z",
  "duration_seconds": 750,
  "total_questions": 6,
  "total_reasks": 1
}
```

### `messages` — Every message between avatar and user
```json
{
  "_id": "msg_001",
  "session_id": "session_abc123",
  "role": "avatar",
  "content": "How are you feeling right now, in this moment?",
  "question_index": 1,
  "llm_action": null,
  "timestamp": "2026-03-07T10:00:05Z"
}
```
```json
{
  "_id": "msg_002",
  "session_id": "session_abc123",
  "role": "user",
  "content": "I have been feeling stressed about work lately",
  "question_index": 1,
  "llm_action": "ACKNOWLEDGE",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-07T10:00:35Z"
}
```

### `scripts` — Pre-defined question sets
```json
{
  "_id": "script_daily_checkin",
  "name": "Daily Check-In",
  "questions": [
    {"order": 1, "text": "How are you feeling right now?", "max_reasks": 2},
    {"order": 2, "text": "What has been on your mind?", "max_reasks": 2}
  ],
  "is_active": true
}
```

